														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1766805">
									

<p>Sorry Roget, this doesn't really do it for me. It's cool, yeah, but there's little substance to it, and parts are just being silly in the pursuit of coolness. Particularly:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>SCP-001 designates the source of all anomalous artifacts classified as Keter</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Well then. There's a lot of Keters (including both of mine, incidentally), that this makes absolutely no sense for. More to the point, it treats &quot;SCP&quot;, and worse, &quot;Keter&quot;, as though this is an intrinsic quality to an object, rather than just the Foundation's terminology. Considering the truly phenomenal range of articles we have on the site, this is simply incoherent.</p>
<p>On the other hand, there were some good parts of this. I liked the collapsed addendum with the letter, although &quot;Level 6 Clearance&quot; made me roll my eyes. Also, the line:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Can't fit round pegs in square holes.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>is brilliant, and as the first line of this I saw, gave me such high hopes. It's definitely a cool evolution of Emberstrom's (though I still think Scantron's is among the best 001 proposals), but it does certain things that mean that I cannot in good conscience upvote it.</p>

							</div>

								
					
