<p>That one is actually clever. 140 neutralizes 505 by absorbing all of its ink, and 505 neutralizes 140 be creating one gigantic new entry. As the 140's effect activates only once the entry is finished (at least in the scope of this proposal), and since 505 never stops writing, 140 can't activate.</p>

